        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "RFC: Doctor health upgrades",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds an RFC for the Doctor health upgrade model we are using across the Doctor stack:\n\n- core Doctor contribution order remains the source of truth for built-in checks\n- the health registry remains the extension health surface\n- rules can migrate in place by adding structured health beside legacy run\n- detect/repair and structured run are both supported migration forms\n- dry-run repair previews can return findings, diffs, effects, warnings, and changes\n\n## Scope\n\nThis is intentionally scoped to Doctor health execution and migration mechanics. It does not define policy semantics or propose public plugin SDK changes.\n\n## Example\n\nThe RFC calls out the shell completion migration shape from #85566: structured lint health is declared through the existing Doctor contribution while real repair remains on the legacy Doctor path.\n",
